08:57.971 --> 09:08.547
[ Beating intensifies ]
[ Dramatic music playing ]
Bobby.

09:08.682 --> 09:13.953
Bobby, come on, man!
We got to go. [ Knocking ]
Bobby!

09:14.087 --> 09:19.792
[ Knocking on door ]
What?
The hell you mean, "what"?

09:19.927 --> 09:23.796
We got a meeting with Greg and
Bernd in like two minutes, man!
What are you doing?

09:23.931 --> 09:28.134
[ Sighs ]
What you think I'm doing?
I'm sleeping.

09:28.268 --> 09:30.870
Yeah.
Looks like you doing a
hell a lot more than just

09:31.004 --> 09:33.472
sleeping, man.
Bobby, look -- look.
Look at me.

09:33.607 --> 09:36.609
Can you just throw some clothes
on and meet me downstairs, like,
ASAP?

09:36.743 --> 09:43.783
Please? A'ight?
And brush your damn teeth, ma--
[ Sighs ]

09:43.917 --> 09:50.556
[ Sighs ]
[ Liquid pouring ]
I'm telling you,

09:50.691 --> 09:55.695
last night was incredible.
The production value, the crowd,
the music -- incredible.

09:55.829 --> 09:59.966
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, yeah, yeah, Bernd.
You think everything that we do

10:00.100 --> 10:05.371
is incredible.
Mmh. For real.
But last night...

10:05.505 --> 10:11.043
Excellent!
Man, what are we doing here?
I mean, seriously.

10:11.178 --> 10:16.649
Glad you finally coming down
to join us.
Bobby, you got to stop

10:16.783 --> 10:21.220
coming onstage late.
I know what you doing, man.
Greg, it doesn't matter.

10:21.355 --> 10:26.892
Yes, it does matter.
This not the Bobby DeBarge Show
featuring Switch.

10:27.027 --> 10:32.365
[ Chuckles ] It's not?
We go onstage as a group.

10:35.335 --> 10:38.404
Bernd.
Hm?
So, what's up? Huh?

10:38.538 --> 10:42.074
Is Motown footing the bill to
fly my family out here?
What?

10:42.209 --> 10:47.847
Probably not.
Okay. All right.
Then ask Jermaine Jackson

10:47.981 --> 10:51.650
to fly them out here, okay?
He's the one that
got us our deal.

10:51.785 --> 10:57.289
Maybe he can get them one, too.
Maybe.
But I don't know that we want to

10:57.424 --> 11:04.096
keep going back to that well.
Asking favors and whatnot.
Favors?

11:04.231 --> 11:09.235
No, every time we step on that
stage, they all make money.
Money off of us, Bernd.

11:09.369 --> 11:16.108
Okay? Now that's a damn favor.
Calm down, okay, Bobby?
Listen, Bobby...

11:16.243 --> 11:21.380
I understand what you're saying.
I do.
And I will get your people out

11:21.515 --> 11:25.851
here, even if I have to fly them
out and put them up myself.
I just hope they're worth the

11:25.986 --> 11:29.388
price of admission.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
Hold on.

11:29.523 --> 11:33.225
Ain't no question, now,
our family can go, a'ight,
Bernd?

11:33.360 --> 11:38.130
Randy sings and plays the bass
just like me.
Mark has skills on the trumpet.

11:38.265 --> 11:42.768
And Bunny, she is beautiful.
I'm talking about sings
and writes music.

11:42.903 --> 11:45.204
And then we got El.
[ Chuckles ]
Tell him.

11:45.338 --> 11:49.508
That little Negro can do
everything.
And not to mention,

11:49.643 --> 11:55.581
they all are DeBarges,
so you know they extra pretty,
just like me and Bobby here.

11:55.715 --> 12:04.657
[ Chuckles ]
Tell him.
Bobby, what's the matter?

12:04.791 --> 12:08.661
Bernd,
I'm still tripping off that
whole "favor" comment, man.

12:08.795 --> 12:11.097
Oh, Bobby --
Ain't nobody gave me nothing,
Bernd.

12:11.231 --> 12:15.101
Ain't nobody gave me nothing!
Bobby! Relax!
No, no, no. Listen.

12:15.235 --> 12:20.873
Listen, I write. I sing.
Those women are screaming
my name, okay?

12:21.007 --> 12:26.779
I earn every damn penny that
they're barely paying us, okay?
So if you want to keep your job

12:26.913 --> 12:31.283
as manager, you better not say
that favor thing no more.
Do you understand me?

12:31.418 --> 12:35.488
Do you understand me?
I run this show!
Oh, you run this?

12:35.622 --> 12:41.861
I started this group, Bobby.
Not you.
Yeah. Blow me off.

12:41.995 --> 12:46.398
This guy shows up 2.5 hours
late to the show,
is late to rehearsals,

12:46.533 --> 12:52.404
doesn't make other shows,
but now he run everything.
I already apologized for

12:52.539 --> 12:58.677
being late, Greg, all right?
Everybody was cool with it.
But you.

12:58.812 --> 13:02.348
I don't know what you want me to
say, Greg.
We can't keep doing this,

13:02.482 --> 13:07.953
this -- this circle thing,
you know, round and around.
I mean, the fellas,

13:08.088 --> 13:11.390
they starting to lose patience
with you.
Can't you see what you're doing

13:11.525 --> 13:16.395
to the group?
Group?
If it wasn't for me and Tommy,

13:16.530 --> 13:20.966
there would be no group, Greg!
There would be no Switch.
Is that right?

13:21.101 --> 13:25.137
That's absolutely right.
Those women ain't screaming
your name, man.

13:25.272 --> 13:31.143
[ Scoffs ]
Check this out, Greg. Okay.
Hey, you -- how 'bout --

13:31.278 --> 13:35.714
h-how 'bout we do this, a'ight?
You let me concentrate on my
life, okay.

13:35.849 --> 13:42.054
You -- you let me concentrate on
mine, and I'll let you lie to
the ladies that you a DeBarge.

13:42.189 --> 13:46.659
'Cause -- 'cause we all know
that's the only way you gonna
get your sorry ass laid, okay?

13:46.793 --> 13:50.229
That's unless I give you a few
of my leftovers.
Boy, you know what --

13:50.363 --> 13:53.532
No! No. No, no, no.
Hold on up now, Greg.
Be cool.

13:53.667 --> 13:57.303
I love you, bro. You know I do.
But don't let this light-skinned
thing fool you now.

14:05.278 --> 14:12.585
Yeah.
Bobby D.
Well, I'll see you at rehearsal.

14:12.719 --> 14:19.325
That's if you decide to show up.
G... [ Exclaims ]
[ Sighs ]

14:19.459 --> 14:22.228
Get him.
I-I'll handle this.
[ Stammers ] I got it.

14:22.362 --> 14:24.263
Greg! Gregory!

14:27.968 --> 14:32.404
Greg is your friend, man.
Listen, let me make one thing
clear, a'ight?

14:32.539 --> 14:36.709
Greg is about Greg.
He ain't my friend,
and he ain't yours.

14:36.843 --> 14:40.312
No, no, no, man.
You got to stop this.
You got to stop being so

14:40.447 --> 14:46.318
goddamn mad all the time.
You starting to sound just --
You're starting to sound

14:46.453 --> 14:52.524
just like him.
Let's not talk about
your father.

14:52.659 --> 14:58.163
>> <i> Our</i> father, Bobby.
And you know that I'm right.
Man, I-I don't want to

14:58.298 --> 15:03.202
hear this, man, a'ight?
Listen to me.
I don't know if you inherited

15:03.336 --> 15:07.573
some of his traits or not, but
you happy one second, and then
you all mad the next.

15:14.881 --> 15:19.952
♪♪
[ Lighter flicks ]

15:25.025 --> 15:27.793
♪♪

15:33.933 --> 15:42.408
Bobby, you keep that dress
on, you little sissy.
♪♪

15:47.480 --> 15:53.152
Listen to me.
We can't let the past survive,
Bobby.

15:53.286 --> 15:59.825
We can't.
We have to bury it.
And bury it deep.

15:59.959 --> 16:10.336
Because if we don't,
our past is gonna be burying us.
Come here, man.

16:10.470 --> 16:17.609
Go on upstairs, man.
Tommy.
Yeah?

16:21.314 --> 16:26.885
I love you, too, man.
♪♪

16:29.489 --> 16:32.257
♪♪

16:36.863 --> 16:41.734
[ Telephone rings ]
[ Groans ]

16:46.873 --> 16:50.309
Hey.
Hey, you.
Bunny! Bunny-bun.

16:50.443 --> 16:54.113
What's going on?
Nothing.
Didn't think I'd catch you.

16:54.247 --> 16:57.916
You're always gone.
Aye, I'm always working.
Always working.

16:58.051 --> 17:02.955
Even now, I'm sitting here in a
sea of lyrics, trying to make
sense of it all, you know?

17:03.089 --> 17:06.925
Well, I'll be there
to help you soon.
Actually, I'm finishing

17:07.060 --> 17:09.862
packing now.
Oh, man.
That's -- that's great.

17:09.996 --> 17:13.766
I can't wait to see you guys.
Me and Tommy miss you guys,
for real.

17:13.900 --> 17:17.770
We miss you two knuckleheads,
too.
Speaking of knuckleheads,

17:17.904 --> 17:21.106
where's your brothers?
Oh, you know.
Out saying their goodbyes to

17:21.241 --> 17:24.777
their little girlfriends and
whatnot.
I don't even know if

17:24.911 --> 17:28.714
they packed yet.
They'll be fine.
They'll get it together.

17:33.520 --> 17:41.660
What's going on, Bun?
You sound quiet.
I guess I'm a little nervous.

17:41.795 --> 17:46.465
I want things to work out
for us out there.
I really do.

17:46.599 --> 17:52.538
I want things to change.
Change for the better.
It will.

17:52.672 --> 17:57.876
I promise.
[ Sighs ]
We just got to stay together.

17:58.011 --> 18:01.447
Okay?
Stay close.
You know what I'm saying?

18:01.581 --> 18:05.417
Yes.
Like Mama used to say.
Like a fist.

18:05.552 --> 18:10.355
What's that?
Like a fist.
Remember, Mama used to tell us

18:10.490 --> 18:17.429
that when we were little?
[ Children chanting "Fight!" ]
Get off!

18:17.564 --> 18:21.900
Get off of him.
Get off of him.
Now, what is going on?

18:22.035 --> 18:26.505
He was hitting the keys.
We were trying to play a song.
All right. [ Sighs ]

18:26.639 --> 18:31.009
Now, I want you all
to calm down.
Look at me.

18:31.144 --> 18:37.015
You see my hand, here?
You see my fingers?
You see how they wiggle and move

18:37.150 --> 18:41.753
and want to dance around?
You see that?
You see, I don't want y'all to

18:41.888 --> 18:49.995
be like wiggling fingers.
I need you to be more like this.
Like a fist.

18:50.129 --> 18:59.338
Together. Close. Strong.
Always ready to protect
one another.

18:59.472 --> 19:06.211
To help one another.
To love one another.
You see, wiggling fingers

19:06.346 --> 19:10.048
get broken real easy when
they're out there
wiggling by themselves.

19:10.183 --> 19:16.722
But a fist? Oh, ho.
It's hard to break up a fist
when it's tight,

19:16.856 --> 19:23.128
when it's together.
When it has a purpose.
All right?

19:23.263 --> 19:26.965
Let me see your fists.
Come on. Bring it together.
All right.

19:27.100 --> 19:33.639
That's what I'm talking about.
There you go.
Now get back to playing music.

19:33.773 --> 19:37.576
She won't say it, but she's
gonna miss us when we leave.
She'll be fine.

19:37.710 --> 19:42.681
She always is.
Well, you finish packing,
all right?

19:42.815 --> 19:45.617
I'll see you soon, sis.
Love you.
Love you, too.

19:45.752 --> 19:51.290
All right.
♪♪

19:56.863 --> 20:02.534
That's the one, baby.
Yessir.
Yo!

20:02.669 --> 20:08.674
Bobby.
Come on, man!
[ Laughs ]

20:12.912 --> 20:18.283
[ Inaudible ]
Oh, here we go.
How many DeBarges are there?

20:18.418 --> 20:24.423
Including the ones still in
Michigan, 10.
Okay.

20:24.557 --> 20:30.996
How many of them can sing?
[ Snorts softly ]
All of 'em.

20:34.601 --> 20:39.638
[ Chuckling ]
Honestly, guys,
I'm glad you're here, man.

20:39.772 --> 20:42.608
For real.
Yeah.
And I-I'm just ready to get this

20:42.742 --> 20:44.576
party started.
Mm-hmm.
You know what I mean?

20:44.711 --> 20:48.280
Y'all -- y'all ready?
Uh, what?
I said a-are y'all ready?

20:48.414 --> 20:52.751
Are y'all ready to get in there?
I-in where?
In there?

20:52.885 --> 20:57.422
Like right now?
Like right now.
That's what the hell y'all came

20:57.557 --> 21:01.059
out here to do, isn't it?
Isn't it?
Heh...

21:01.194 --> 21:05.097
Well, here's your
opportunity.
What y'all gonna do?

21:08.601 --> 21:13.505
Hey. Hey, hey.
Kill those nerves, all right?
We got you.

21:13.640 --> 21:18.710
Look, just --
just go back to us singing in
the living room, okay?

21:18.845 --> 21:25.917
Wild and free.
[ Vocalizing ]
Hey!

21:26.052 --> 21:30.489
How much goddamn noise y'all
gonna make down here?
Huh?

21:30.623 --> 21:34.026
I can hear you all the way from
the front porch.
Sorry, Daddy.

21:34.160 --> 21:36.762
We were just singing,
playing group.
Mm.

21:36.896 --> 21:43.502
Well, play something else,
then, huh.
Y'all too damn loud.

21:43.636 --> 21:52.344
Where'd your mother go?
She went to church.
Mm.

21:52.478 --> 22:02.020
Hmm. Okay.
Hm.
Well, keep it down in here, huh?

22:02.155 --> 22:07.259
Uh, Bunny, why don't you come
help me out, straighten out the
attic.

22:07.393 --> 22:09.361
Just for a little while, huh?

22:13.499 --> 22:18.937
Come on, now.
Come on.
No.

22:19.072 --> 22:23.942
Hey.
You got a problem, Bobby?
Hmm?

22:24.077 --> 22:29.981
Something on your mind, son?
If there's something on your
mind, son, I'd really like to

22:30.116 --> 22:37.322
hear it.
I'd really like to hear what you
have to say to me.

22:37.457 --> 22:44.396
Mm-hmm.
No? Nothing?
Hmm?

22:44.530 --> 22:49.367
That's okay.
[ Snorts quietly ]
See, your lips aren't moving,

22:49.502 --> 22:57.576
but your eyes --
oh, your eyes are telling me
everything.

22:57.710 --> 23:07.252
They're saying,
"I want to be a hero."
Is that it, Bobby?

23:07.386 --> 23:15.127
Is that what it is, son, hm?
You want to save everyone from
big bad Daddy, here, huh?

23:15.261 --> 23:19.998
The one who puts food in your
mouths and clothes on your
backs?

23:20.133 --> 23:30.308
Is that it? Huh?
Yeah.
I know it is.

23:30.443 --> 23:39.951
When you're done ridding the
world from the likes of me,
who's gonna be your hero, Bobby,

23:40.086 --> 23:49.227
hm?
Who's gonna save you?!
Who's gonna save you, Bobby?!

23:49.362 --> 23:53.365
Hmm?
Yeah.

24:00.439 --> 24:04.476
[ Sighs ]
Bunny.

24:18.124 --> 24:20.892
♪♪

24:26.065 --> 24:28.834
♪♪

24:34.040 --> 24:36.808
♪♪

24:42.114 --> 24:48.286
♪♪
It's only as scary
as you make it to be.

24:48.421 --> 24:52.090
Just -- just go back to us
singing in the living room.
♪ Singin' in the

24:52.225 --> 24:57.062
living room ♪
[ Laughs ] Now that's it.
All right, guys. Y'all ready?

24:57.196 --> 24:59.531
All right, let's go!
Come on.
Family, baby.

24:59.665 --> 25:04.002
Let's go, y'all.
Let's go, let's go.
[ Laughs ]

25:04.136 --> 25:05.804
Oh, this is good.
Uh-huh.

25:06.222 --> 25:13.128
[ Inaudible ]
♪♪
You know they gonna want them

25:13.262 --> 25:19.301
to sing backup for us, right?
You know it's coming.
This how it starts, Bernd.

25:19.435 --> 25:24.372
How what starts?
The beginning of the end.

25:28.144 --> 25:50.865
♪♪
♪♪
♪♪

25:51.000 --> 25:54.002
Hey, Daddy!
What took y'all so long?
Oh, we had to stop by

25:54.136 --> 25:57.138
Catherine.
Where my grandkids?
I thought you was bringing them.

25:57.273 --> 25:59.441
No, they went swimming at a
neighbor's.
Jermaine.

25:59.575 --> 26:02.010
Mm.
You got a real hit with that
Switch, boy.

26:02.144 --> 26:07.315
Yes, sir, we do.
But, Berry, you got to
see the whole family.

26:07.450 --> 26:11.553
Tell him, Hazel.
They all can sing.
Daddy, they're great.

26:11.687 --> 26:16.491
Seriously.
Okay, then.
Set up a showcase.

26:16.626 --> 26:20.095
I'll check them out.
But I wish you would have
brought my grandbabies.

26:20.229 --> 26:27.669
♪♪
Chico, baby, do me a favor
and go check on the twins in the

